description: Dr. Fahad Al-Rashed has joined the computational modeling group in Saudi Aramco’s Research and Development Center (R&DC) in February 2015 as a numerical analyst specializing in partial differential equations (PDEs) in general and the Navier-Stokes equation and high-performance solvers in Computational Fluid Dynamics (CFD) in particular. Dr. Al-Rashed joined the group after completing his Ph.D. (2015) in Mathematics from Texas A&M University where he developed a new highly accurate numerical method and massively parallel software to run CFD simulations. Before that, Dr. Al-Rashed was responsible of designing and deploying the R&DC high-performance computing cluster as computer scientist specializing in high-performance computing and machine learning. Dr. Al-Rashed current research interests includes numerical analysis, scientific computing, CFD and mathematical software. Dr. Al-Rashed is a member of the American Mathematical Society and the Society of Petroleum Engineers.

headline: Machine Learning |  Artificial Intelligence | | Data Scientist | | Computer Scientist | Software Engineer
description:
As I grew older I began to realize that, learning gives me the most joy. Knowing the finite knowledge I can obtain led me to develop a passion for AI and Data. The fact that, I can build what can learn from experiences/data, was exciting to me.

The more I explored and grew my knowledge, I slowly started realizing; if these principles and technology were applied in the world, how beneficial it would be in helping business and bettering the word. The hunger for my knowledge grew and I began creating my own Experimental Designs even after my college years were over. 

The ability to create an object which can learn from data, experiences, benefit its surroundings and humanity gave me the push to not only build/understand those objects, but also to understand how we humans make decisions and learn, so that one day, we can mimic that perfectly. 

Such Agents can use data in businesses, Bio-Engineering, Health and many more to drive decisions towards what is beneficial.

headline: Data scientist
Ph.D. Candidate at KSU | Lecturer | Researcher | Data Scientist
Clinical Genomics Researcher | Genetic and Genomic Counsellor | Academic Teaching Fellow | Executive Business Manager | Bioinformatician & Multi-Omics Data Scientist
company: kaust (king abdullah university of science and technology)
company2: KAUST (King Abdullah University of Science and Technology)
schoolDegree: Doctor of Philosophy - PhD، Cancer Genetics & Genomics (Neuro-Oncology) - School of Medicine
schoolDegree2: Master's degree، MSc Genetic and Genomic Counselling
description:
Experienced Academic with 7+ years of teaching and research experience in the higher education industry in the fields of Genomic Medicine (Genomics, Epigenomics, Transcriptomics, Proteomics, and Metabolomics). Worked as a teaching and research fellow at The University of Leeds in the UK prior to recently starting a new position at a leading scientific research institution in Saudi, King Abdullah University of Science and Technology (KAUST). Graduated from the University of Nottingham in the UK with a First-Class Bachelor’s Degree with Honours in Medical Genetics and a PhD in Genomic Medicine (Cancer Genetics/Neuro-Oncology) which was funded by a Scholarship from the School of Medicine at Nottingham University.  

As a licensed project manager in the UK (PRINCE2 practitioner), Dr Huda Alfardus has been extensively involved in designing, managing, and delivering training programs for pre-university students, undergraduate students, postgraduate students, and university staff. 

She co-founded a 6-figure international training company based in the UK called Internet of Things Academy (IoTA) Ltd, which is dedicated to developing the highest quality training in programming and digital skills. We have reached around 180,000 students from all over the world (across approx. 200 countries) since we started in 2016 and we have helped our students achieve their educational goals, improve their careers and get new jobs in the technology sector. Our courses are highly rated and have been featured as best sellers on top technology education online platforms. 

Now, she has expanded her business activities to KSA, and she has setup 100% Saudi owned company called Raqmiaan (رقمياً) that specialises in providing accredited and international certified digital skills education with a mission to empower the Saudi youth to have fulfilling careers.

Dr Huda Alfardus has held many management and leadership positions in the UK. She was a management board member at the School of Life Sciences at Leeds University and she has sat on the faculty’s promotions panel, and she was a representative board member at LeedsOmics (the genomics research community in the North of England). She served as a peer reviewer for three refereed international journals since 2016 and was a member of the Judges Panel for The Physiological Society. She was an Executive Board member of the SU at Nottingham University, a committee member of The British Science Association, and served a five-year term as a School Governor with Nottingham City Council.

headline: Data Scientist at Insight
schoolDegree: Master of Science - MS, Management Information Systems
schoolDegree2: Bachelor of Science - BS, Business Administration; International Business
description:
I fell in love with Data Science!

My career path has not been the most straightforward. I was offered an opportunity to swim in college and that’s how I moved to the United States. At the time, swimming was my priority and my professional career was just a distant thought in the back of my head. Thus, I never truly stopped to think about what career I wanted to pursue.

During my Bachelor’s I changed my major approximately 5,000 times (and that’s a lowball estimate). After I finished my Bachelor’s, I got myself contemplating life and what I wanted to do with it. I found myself to be a very curious and logical person who likes to solve problems and approaches day-to-day tasks with a scientific view. So, I decided to do my Master’s in Information Systems. 

Throughout my journey in higher education, I fell in love with Data Science for those same reasons. I find it very interesting and exciting to understand and analyze actual phenomena by using scientific methods, processes, and algorithms to extract knowledge and insights from data.

One of my favorite classes during my Master’s was Business Intelligence. In that class, we were assigned to read the book “Hands-On Predictive Analytics with Python” by Alvaro Fuentes, and it really opened my eyes. I loved learning about predictive analytics and using a variety of statistical and quantitative methods to make use of data in order to make predictions.

Now, I find myself diving into books, articles, and Kaggle datasets seeking more knowledge. It was a calling rather than an interest! My specialties include quickly learning new skills, problem-solving, machine learning, Python, PySpark, SQL, and Python libraries including Pandas, NumPy, matplotlib, seaborn, and scikit-learn. I am also well-versed in Tableau, Hadoop, Spark, Git, and GitHub. I’ve started learning other machine learning libraries such as Keras and TensorFlow, and also neural network algorithms and deep learning methods.

If you’re interested in grabbing a coffee (after the pandemic is over, thanks Covid) or connecting, please send a message my way!
jobDescription2: Collaborated on creating an AI model to detect pathologies through Computer Vision in ultrasound images to help medical doctors in Africa

headline: Data Scientist | AI Educator | Software Engineer
description:
I am a Data Scientist at Saudi Commission For Health Specialties. Prior to that, I worked as a Lead Instructor at General Assembly teaching students core machine learning and data driven problem-solving skills. I also designed training courses with multiple local datasets to solve business problems. Students graduated under my mentorship now hold key KSA public and private sector data driven positions.

Before becoming an AI Educator, I worked as an application developer and have developed multiple applications catering to the Insurance Sector. My team developed a Motor Claims System and integrated it with the KSA car insurance Najm. In addition, I developed a document archiving system integrated with the core insurance system and other third party applications.

On the personal front, I have participated in numerous hackathons such as the AI Artathon where my team used deep learning algorithms and drones to create pieces of art. I have also worked on multiple projects such as a neural network based chat bot for Slack and WhatsApp, KSA weather history crawler, sentiment analyzer for hotel reviews, etc.

I graduated from Cairo University with a Bachelors in Computer Engineering. I have vast volunteering experience and extracurricular activities that I have done over the span of five years. For example, I have volunteered with Resala - an orphanage where I used to volunteer every week.

My areas of interest are AI Education | Data Science | Consulting | Insurance Sector | Healthcare | Consumer Goods | Customer Services

My skills include Machine Learning Algorithms | Business Analytics | Data Collection | NLP

Check my latest articles on ML and AI here: medium.com/@esraa.sabry.mohamed

jobDescription:
I worked as a Full Stack Developer in Jeddah at the company headquarters of Almabani, one of the largest and most successful construction companies in the region. 

I was responsible for building, deploying and maintaining web and stand-alone applications and dashboards for our in-house ERP system.  I worked as part of a small team of dedicated programmers that were responsible for the full software development cycle from ideation, design, testing, and rollout and in certain instances in-life support as well. 

Projects often involved collaboration with different departments of a multi-million-dollar company and centred on providing users with the most efficient solutions. List of responsibilities and projects included (but not limited to):

The dashboard showed the current status and cashflow for all present (and past) projects undertaken by the company, with at-a-glance metrics which could be broken down into minute details and exported to excel.

- Document Management System. An interactive online application to allow the tracking and identification of all outgoing and incoming official documents into the head offices through barcodes.

- VAT Invoice Generator. To allow the automatic generation of all VAT invoices following the implementation of VAT in the Kingdom in January 2018.

- Maintenance, update and troubleshooting for users regarding the multitude of Applications available in our in-house ERP system.

- Maintenance and continual updates for the Almabani public website.

headline: Molecular Biology ( Epigenetic )Researcher and Data Scientist
jobTitle: Data Scientist and Molecular Biology Researcher
school: temple university - lewis katz school of medicine
schoolDegree: Post-doctoral research fellowship، Immunology and lung transplant research
description: Ambitious and self-motivated professional with 3 years of experience gained through challenging professional environment. The core of my research focused on translational medicine in epigenetic in pulmonary diseases and neurological degeneration and certified to work in clinical studies and animal model. My passionate with doctoral degree in the area of molecular and cellular biology, epigenetic, gene therapy and inflammatory diseases besides intensive courses in data science and deep learning has enhanced my strength in data analytics, critical thinking, data management, project and time management,decision making, and laboratory experience and self-taught welling to undergo new challenge in critical thinking, decision making, communication, fast find alternative methods and strategy and being as independent researcher and data scientist . working knowledge of data analytics, animal handle and translational medicine aimed to enhance my professional horizons through joining the position and field where i would be able to encounter a new responsibility and drive me to be more innovative.
schoolDescription2: High mobility group nucleosome binding (HMGN) proteins belong to the superfamily of high mobility group (HMG) proteins. HMGN1 (N1) and HMGN2 (N2) were found to be highly expressed in neural stem/progenitor cells in the mouse brain. Here, mouse embryonal carcinoma cells (P19 EC) were used as a model system to study the role of HMGN proteins. The aim was to develop a lentiviral system to investigate the role of this protein in stem cell. N2 knockdown in undifferentiated P19 EC cells resulted in the down regulation of Oct4 protein levels. ChIP assays showed that N2 binding over the Oct4 gene was absent in N2 knockdown cells. Furthermore, the binding of N1 at TSS was increased in the absence of N2. Consistent with the reduction in Oct4 expression, the level of the active histone modification, H3K4me3, were also reduced at the Oct4 gene. These results support the role of N2 in the regulation of Oct4 expression in P19 cells which may be important for maintaining stem cell pluripotency.
schoolDescription: three projects were giving to initiate novel research path focusing on the effect of epigenetic (miRNA, DNA methylation) in COPD and IPF. I had to obtain Three main certificates  to start working with patients samples (Lung), animals, cell lines at the lab. I learned all animal work from modelling to extract cells from human and animal  organ.

Profile  
Dr. Mohammed Khursheed Akhtar has more than 30 years of experience in the field of Teaching, Research, Consulting and IT Business Development. He holds 2 PhDs, from Atlantic International University, Hawaii, USA in 2004-2007 in Geographic Information Systems (GIS) and another from Singhania University Rajasthan, India in 2011-2015 in Enterprise Resource Planning (ERP). He also has a Masters Degree in Applied Mathematics with Honors and has diploma in Islamic Finance and Insurance.  
 
Dr. Akhtar is currently working as a Senior Strategic Advisor & Data Scientist at Research and Studies Unit of Strategic Center to Kingdom Vision Realization of King Abdulaziz University, Jeddah, Kingdom of Saudi Arabia under Kingdom Vision 2030.
 
Designation
He worked as a Data Scientist at KAU Web Observatory for Web Studies from 2017 to 2019; as a Research Fellow at Strategic Department of KAU from 2013 to 2107; as a Deputy Project Manager at KAU-ERP Implementation Project from 2011 to 2012; as a Faculty Member from 2008 to 2011 at Faculty of Commuting and Information Technology and as a GIS Head at Projects and Proposal Department from 2005 to 2008, and Data Based Specialist from 1990 to 2005 in King Abdulaziz University, Jeddah, Saudi Arabia.

Books/Publications 
Author of 5 books (under publication), more than 25 published articles and coauthor of more than 25 articles and conferences publications. He attended several seminars and speaker, Panelist and Moderator of more than 50 conferences and seminars. Recently, he attended more than 350 webinars in this pandemic situation including 15 panelists and 10 moderators works.  
 
Fields of Interest 
Big Data Analytics using R and Python, Machine Learning, Artificial Intelligence, IoT (Internet of Things) Research and Development, Statistical Modelling, ERP (SAP) Architecture and Computer Component-Based Development (CBD), Software Development Methodologies, Risk Management, Geographical Information systems (GIS), Project Management Strategic Planning and Consulting, Islamic Finance and Insurance, Knowledge Management and Consultancy.

schoolDescription2:
Thesis: Hierarchical Document Classification within the Context of the Semantic Web.

An important purposes of the semantic web is to make the available resources clearly organized, structured and machine-identifiable. This facilitates accessing, understanding and linking large data repositories, which can be used in a variety of useful applications; moreover, it allows software agents to process and analyse the data which will likely result in the emergence of new useful information.
In this thesis, an application has been developed to enrich the semantic web with machine-readable description of scientific publications related to the field of computing. This system mainly applies hierarchical classification techniques based on the local binary classifiers (SVM, NB) approach to categorize given documents according to the ACM taxonomy. Evaluating the approaches used in this work shown an improvement over previous work that classifies similar data....
schoolDescription:
A highly selective intensive program that covers probability and statistics, machine learning, data at scale, software engineering and data visualisation for real-world datasets.

– Conducted case studies using real world datasets from well-known companies in the US to solve problems such as fraud detection, churn prediction and other classification and regression problems

– Project: predicting job salaries from approximately 15K scraped job descriptions and correlating discovered latent features (skill-set) with salaries.  This has been done using Non-negating matrix factorization (NMF) to find latent features, and random forest for regression. It attempts to answer the following questions: 
      - How valuable is a skill-set
      - How much the value varies across companies
      - What topics or skills contribute to high salaries

headline: Research Scientist

schoolDegree: Doctor of Philosophy (PhD), Multidisciplinary and statistical approaches for complex systems analysis
schoolDegree2: State Engineer cycle (Ingénieur d’Etat en Automatique), Automatic
skill1: Modeling and analysis of complex systems
description:
Interests
Combining multiple approaches to understanding complex systems using analysis-based simulations or data-driven statistical modeling approaches in different fields of interest including Energy Geosystems, Climate Change and Paleoclimate. Approaches include Bayesian statistical modeling, probabilistic sensitivity and uncertainty analyses, non-parametric time series prediction models, high dimensional data clustering, causality inference, scenario interpolation and space filling designs for complex simulations. 

The focus in ANPERC includes linking the energy sector to the climate and environment fields for realistic predictions, by constraining statistical models with the physics of the system and observational data, analyzing the impact of climate change on the persistence of renewable energies and society resilience in Saudi Arabia and, analyzing the predictability of energy resources and showing their limits and impacts on the environment and climate. 

Methods: Statistical modeling, Bayesian statistics, Probabilistic sensitivity analysis, Gaussian process emulators, Structural Time series models, Clustering, Causality inference, Space filling designs of computer experiments, complex system analysis, non parametric predictive models. 

Actual Applications: Saudi Arabia energy sector, Climate Change impacts, Climate, Renewable and non-renewable energy prediction, Mineral/Metal peak and production predictions.

Objectives
Looking for new challenges in a career path in academia, to highlight my scientific skills and transversal ones including project analysis and management, collaborations creation and networking, and efficient science communication, gained from multidisciplinary experiences.

Profile
Research & Development in modeling and analysis of complex systems. International experiences and collaborations, transfer knowledge and training. Highly independent and open-minded with adaptation and fast learning ability. Ability & interest in combining multiple approaches/methodologies and perspectives to solve complex problems. Thinking out of the box and communicating clearly complex scientific concepts. Strong organization and coordination skills of multiple parallel projects. Excellent people management, team working and inter-cultural communication skills. Strong coordination and influential skills. Networking within and beyond Academia while Connecting minds under multidisciplinary projects (Academic and non academic).

headline: Analytics Lead - Claims Operational Intelligence at Insurance. Analytics Practitioner. Inquisitive Learner. Explorer
schoolDegree2: Bachelor of Arts (BA), International Business Administration
description:
I am an innovative, collaborative, and assertive problem solver with a wide range of experiences working in data analytics, software development and data science in financial services. I am looking for a new leadership opportunity where I can have the autonomy to drive business performance by collaborative development and implementation of human-centred data products and process automation to create new values from data assets to meet the business needs. I value a senior leadership team who can act as a role model to cultivate and uphold a data-centric culture, understand the essential need of upskilling, reward, and recognition to develop and maintain happy, motivated, and productive workforce, and work towards closing the gap between practices and the actual achievement of diversity, inclusion, and equality in the workplace. 

My ambition is to democratise data to enable businesses to accelerate regular, proactive, and insight-driven decisions from self-service analytics platforms. I am also passionate about exploring improvement opportunities through identifying gaps in current business processes, leveraging available data and resources to develop applicable analytical solutions, and getting stakeholders engaged in frequent communications for support, project update and agile decision making to effectively improve productivity.

I enjoy taking new challenges in driving technological and organisational transformation and engaging business leaders to lead through the change by translating into benefit, meaning and purpose behind so that they can build better understanding of the business strategy and their roles to enable success.
jobDescription:
●	I established and owned the team’s growth direction focusing on data workflow automation and self-service analytics to support the fast-paced claims operations to meet our strategic objectives on operations management transformation and data democratisation
●	I led the team to build and deploy the first ever self-service Tableau data platform in the company on a large scale, providing essential operational KPIs to over 120 Claims leaders and commercial executives to identify and detect scenarios relating to inefficiencies, opportunities, and threats, and enabling proactive operational solutions to drive productivity across the entire department. I established good design principles and took ownership of data assurance and governance to protect the company’s reputation and obligations, as well as to strategically control data output to prevent unauthorised disclosure of data currently accessible by a high volume of users. 
●	I redesigned and automated critical Excel reporting in SQL to ~700 colleagues which reduced 4 hours per day from manual data input activities to full automation and enabled the data output to be delivered before 9AM
●	I built a claim workflow forecasting framework that transforms a 20-year-old departmental target operating model. Continued to lead scope and defined analytical solutions to ensure the success of the Test and Learn programme in advance of the department-wide implementation of the resource planning model
●	I introduced new opportunities to develop more in-house software applications to the wider team using cost-effective R Shiny framework to control business processes and improve productivity in other areas of the Claims department
●	I incorporated statistical methods through continual R&D to deliver new Tableau features for effective storytelling and action recommendation. I suggested project teams leverage more hypothesis testing to track the effectiveness of new changes made to improve the Guidewire ClaimCentre system
jobDescription2:
●	I transferred a core underwriting technical pricing model from Emblem to an H2O cluster to optimise the duration and frequency of model training and validation. The process used the xgboost algorithm to predict average claims costs on each policyholder, which predominantly involves hyperparameter tuning through grid search on training and validating several models to find an optimal set of hyperparameters for the particular problem.
●	I worked with senior actuaries to examine and compare the best-performing predictive models using ggplot2 in R to identify strengths and weaknesses in the prediction power of each model to decide the final model, or to re-train the models with a different approach to improving the model fit and performance.
●	I liaised with a wide range of colleagues in deploying the R Shiny application into production. I documented the complex algorithms in a flowchart in Visio to illustrate the offer calculations and the code for handover to the solutions architect and development team to build the Guidewire ClaimCentre application in Javascript.
●	I peer-reviewed existing project documentations and model scripts produced by other data scientists in R to improve code quality, examine data integrity, and verify model assumption and validation. As part of this, I built a new data dictionary for a vehicle database in Python (json).

headline: Petroleum Consultant | Energy Economist | Data Scientist | Visiting Professor | Author | Speaker
company: king fahd university of petroleum & minerals
description:
I was a Corporate Energy and Economic Consultant at Saudi Aramco. I was also a visiting professor in Petroleum Engineering Department at King Fahd University of Petroleum & Minerals (KFUPM). Prior to this position, I was Director and Fellow of Global Energy Markets and Economics Research at King Abdullah Petroleum Studies and Research Center (KAPSARC) from 2008 to 2013. I have a prolific work experience with Saudi Aramco working in various departments including strategy & market analysis, reservoir management, upstream strategy development and reserves assessment, oil & gas fields integrated development studies, reservoir simulation, and reservoir engineering systems. 
 
I hold one U.S. patent, published over 40 technical papers in peer-reviewed journals and conference proceedings, and authored/co-authored three books: “Artificial Intelligence and Data Mining Applications in the E&P Industry,” “Carbon Capture and Storage: Technologies, Policies, Economics, and Implementation Strategies,” and “Innovative Methods for Analyzing and Forecasting World Gas Supply.” I am a member of the Society of Petroleum Engineers (SPE), and International Association for Energy Economics (IAEE). 

I am a technical editor/reviewer for the journals of SPE Reservoir Evaluation & Engineering, Energy Policy, and Natural Gas Science and Engineering. I was Chairman of the 2007 SPE Saudi Arabia Annual Technical Symposium, and Vice Chairman of the 2006 version. I was a key speaker and an executive member of the Organizing and Technical Committees of the 2011 1st KAPSARC Energy Dialogue, Riyadh, Saudi Arabia.

I earned my Ph.D. with distinction from Texas A&M University, and M.S. and B.S. degrees with honors from KFUPM, all in petroleum engineering. I also hold Executive MBA degree with honors from Prince Muhammad University (PMU), KSA.

أهداف العمل:
الأهداف هي مجموعة من النتائج النهائية التي تسعى المؤسسات المدنية عبر إداراتها إلى تحقيقها، وهي في الغالب تحقيق أكبر قدر من الربح بأقل كلفة ممكنة كما تشمل التوسع المستقبلي وارتفاع نسبة البيع والإبقاء على التقدم أمام المنافسة. كما للعسكريين أهداف يسعون لتحقيقها سواء في السلم أو الحرب. أما على المستوى الأشمل فإن للدول أهداف تحددها إستراتيجيتها الوطنية.

الهدف هو ما يسعى إليه الفرد من أجل تحقيقه الأهداف هي أساس حياتنا فمن منا لم يكن لديه هدف في حياته ويريد تحقيقه سواء كان هدفنا الدراسة والنجاح أو العمل والأستحقاق ولدينا أهداف كثيرة بحياتنا الهدف هو نهاية علمية لبداية نظرية لتحقيق الغاية والمراد منها أنجاز شيء ما والافتخار به اي انه تحقيق لاراده قوية الهدف هو النتيجة الحاسمة التي يسعى إليها الشخص الهدف له معان كثيرة منها أنها الغاية والخيار الأخير الذي يرغب الشخص بالوصول إليه كما يعبر الهدف انه الأنجاز المتحقق على أرض الواقع والأهداف كثيرة بحياتنا فكل شخص لديه هدف.

Business objectives:

The goals are a set of final results that civil institutions seek through their administrations to achieve, which are usually to achieve the largest amount of profit at the lowest possible cost. They also include future expansion, high sales, and maintaining progress in front of competition. The military also has goals that they seek to achieve, whether in peace or war. On the broader level, countries have goals that are determined by their national strategy.

The goal is what the individual strives to achieve in order to achieve the goals are the basis of our life. Who among us does not have a goal in his life and wants to achieve it, whether our goal is study and success or work and merit, and we have many goals in our life. That is, it is the fulfillment of a strong will. The goal is the decisive result that the target person seeks. It has many meanings, including that it is the end and the last option that the person wishes to reach. The goal also expresses that it is the achievement on the ground of reality, and the goals are many in our life, so every person has a goal.

ترويج المبيعات (بالإنجليزية: Sales promotion)‏ هو أحد الجوانب الأربعة من المزيج الترويجي. (أما الأجزاء الثلاثة الأخرى من المزيج الترويجي هي الإعلان، البيع الشخصي، والدعاية / العلاقات العامة). اتصالات التسويق عبر وسائل الإعلام وعبر غير وسائل الإعلام تعمل لوقت محدد سلفا لزيادة الطلب على السلع الاستهلاكية، وتحفيز الطلب في السوق أو تحسين المنتج المتوافر. ومن الأمثلة على ذلك :

تنظيم المسابقات.
عرض نقاط الشراء.
عمل الخصومات (التسويق).
حرية السفر، مثل الرحلات المجانية.
ترويج المبيعات يمكن تطبيقه سواء على العملاء، موظفي المبيعات، أو أعضاء قناة التوزيع (مثل تجار التجزئة). المبيعات الترويجية التي تستهدف المستهلك تسمى ترويج المبيعات الاستهلاكية. الحملات الترويجية التي تستهدف مبيعات التجزئة والجملة تسمى ترويج المبيعات التجارية. بعض المبيعات الترويجية ولا سيما التي تتبع منها أساليب غير عادية، وتعتبر وسيلة للتحايل من قبل العديد من الناس.

description:
I was leading a fairly normal life having grown up in Makkah, and later studying medicine at King Abdul Aziz University in Jeddah.

While in the college , I was always looking for ways to let off steam to relieve me from the stress of my demanding schedule.

Lastly, I decided to try diving for many reasons may be because I grew up listening to my father’s fascinating stories about the Red Sea, or may be because diving in Saudi Arabia was an unconventional activity—which only motivated me to pursue it more.

By the time I finished my medical internship, I have earned my first scuba diving certification. But with my demanding work schedule which prevent me from furthering my diving career.

One day, when me and my friends were discussing the very challenging North Pole dive—only two women in the world have accomplished this feat. “The idea to dive at the North Pole seemed not only unique and interesting, but also a challenge that would define me. I wanted to be the first Arab woman to do so,” and this is what I did.

headline: Associate Professor in Bioinformatics at King Abdulaziz City for Science and Technology
company: king abdulaziz city for science and technology
jobTitle: Research  Associate Professor at The National Center for Agricultural Technology
company2: King Abdulaziz City for Science and Technology
jobTitle2: Manager, The National Centre for Bioinformatics
description:
Research Associate Professor in the Bioinformatics lab at the King Abdulaziz City for Science and Technology, working on biological data analysis including insects, animals, and plants. Recent projects include the Date Plam Pest Genomics project; a large-scale genomics project to build high-quality draft assemblies and annotate gene content for major date palm pests like Red Plam Weevil. 

The project will use whole-genome sequencing approaches to understand genetic variation in the red palm weevil (Rhynchophorus ferrugineus) in Saudi Arabia. I also led a team in the development of the first national antimicrobial resistance surveillance platform in Saudi Arabia. This project consists of developing a national database to monitor infectious diseases in Saudi Arabia's health facilities, leverage existing data, and develop infectious disease diagnosis research. This work is part of an ongoing collaboration between the King Abdulaziz City for Science and Technology, Riyadh, Saudi Arabia, and the Public Health Authority (Weqaya), Ministry of Health, Saudi Arabia.

I completed a Ph.D. funded by the King Abdulaziz City for Science and Technology in Bioinformatics. The Ph.D. was undertaken in Casey Bergman's lab and involved conducting research on Nonodong DNA in one of the most important model organisms Drosophila melanogaster that includes using non-reference transposable elements (TEs) to test the cold spot hypothesis on conserved noncoding elements (CNEs).
jobDescription:
Working on Camel Genomics project:
This project aimed to study the genome structure of camels and develop genetic chips that contain different genetic variations in camel breeds to select the camel phenotype at early stages such as beauty or milk production using whole-genome sequencing. This work is part of an ongoing collaboration between the King Abdulaziz City for Science and Technology, Riyadh, Saudi Arabia, Ministry of Environment, Water and Agriculture of Saudi Arabia, and King Saud University, Riyadh, Saudi Arabia.
jobDescription2:
Worked on the first national antimicrobial resistance surveillance platform:
Antimicrobial resistance threatens advancement in medicine and responsiveness to dangers of infectious diseases. The project consists of developing a national database to monitor infectious diseases in Saudi Arabia's health facilities, leverage existing data and develop infectious disease diagnosis research. The platform analyzes infectious diseases’ data and reports statistical indicators to policy makers and the World Health Organization (WHO). It monitors reported infections in healthcare facilities across the Kingdom and generates risk assessment reports accordingly. The project will be vital to reduce incidence of infectious diseases and to develop effective vaccines and antibiotics against antibiotic resistant microorganisms. This work is part of an ongoing collaboration between the King Abdulaziz City for Science and Technology, Riyadh, Saudi Arabia and the Public Health Authority (Weqaya), Ministry of Health, Saudi Arabia.

headline: Assistant Professor of Computational Linguistics at King Abdulaziz University
schoolDegree: Doctor of Philosophy - PhD، Computational Linguistics
description:
Dr. Emad Alghamdi Is an Assistant Professor of computational linguistics in King Abdulaziz University. He is the founding director of AI in Language Learning & Assessment Lab (www.ailla.tech). His research interests include video complexity and the use of artificial intelligence in language learning, assessment, and research. He obtained his PhD from the University of Melbourne with a thesis entitled "Automated Video Difficulty Assessment", under the supervision of Dr. Paul Gruba (Applied Linguistics) and Dr. Eduardo Velloso (Computer Science). In his PhD research, Emad used advance machine learning algorithms to develop computational models for predicting video difficulty for language learners. During his PhD research, Emad worked as a research data intern at the Melbourne Data
Analytics Platform (MDAP) and was a member of the Human-Computer
Interaction Group at the university. He has published numerous studies and
book chapters in top venues such as LL&T and IJCALL. 

Emad is passionate about developing innovative technologies for language
learning, assessment, and research. His recent projects are the Automated
Video Analysis (AUVANA) software---a cross platform desktop application
for extracting, commuting, and visualizing visual complexity in videos---and
a virtual crowdsourcing platform for question items development
(CrowdyQ).

description:
An aspiring clinician-scientist. Although these two align in many aspects, they come to differ in others, too. On becoming a physician, most safest and most efficient options are the top priority for patients care. Whereas as a scientist, experimenting and discovering come first. Delving into these two aspects have brought me balance and great satisfaction. Both require different mindsets and not just knowledge to apply. Serving Humanity is a shared goal and a privilege of these two entities.

Becoming a genetic epidemiologist and scientist has expanded my perspective. The current shift in health care to more individually designed management brings challenge and excitement. Also, dealing with genetic data using bioinformatics and their databases for research and clinical purposes truly awakens the detective in you. Omics technologies have a great potential in advancing knowledge and bringing better care for everyone. Mastering them is a goal of mine and delving into new perspectives is a pleasure. 

Building skills that are essential for both wet and dry laboratory has been a great key for opportunities and enjoying experiments. Especially that of molecular and cellular biology and currently expanding on microbiology and immunology to study new perspectives and angles in clinical and experimental researches.

headline: Printed electronics scientist & engineer.  Energy harvesting, advanced manufacturing, and technology transfer,
school: kaust (king abdullah university of science and technology)
schoolDegree: Doctor of Philosophy - PhD، Materials Science and Engineering
school2: KAUST (King Abdullah University of Science and Technology)
schoolDegree2: Master of Science (MSc) ، Materials Science and Engineering
description:
👋🏽 Hello, my name is Daniel

🎓 Soon to graduate with a PhD in Materials Science and Engineering from KAUST (May 2022)

🌇 Native from Mexico city, I am passionate about Industry 4.0 and scalable manufacturing of new materials for energy harvesting, energy storage, and sensing.

📚 Graduated with a mechanical engineering degree, I started my career managing manufacturing lines for the automotive industry. Then I moved into the development of client relations and contract management based on strategic KPIs for refractories in steel manufacturing. Now, I work on developing strategies to fabricate printed organic photovoltaics and sensors via additive manufacturing processes .

💻 In the near future, i'm looking to work as an engineering lead in a diverse team to develop technology transfer and innovation strategies for energy harvesting and energy storage. 

🏔 In my free time, you can find me running, DJing, or producing electronic music. 

💪🏽 Proven problem-solving, Research and Development, Business Strategy Development, Cross-functional collaboration, Science Communication, Innovation Leadership, Technology Development
jobDescription:
I always had an interest in energy harvesting and how new technologies transition from discovery to application.

In this role as a Materials Scientist, my focus is the development of 2D and 3D printed solar cells, thermoelectric generators, super-capacitors and batteries, photodetectors and sensors for IoT applications based on coating, inkjet printing, and other additive manufacturing techniques. 

My main activities include the design of experiments, data collection and analysis, the formation of key scientific figures, writing scientific manuscripts and research proposals, and presenting results in international conferences and workshops. 

I coordinated and collaborated with multidisciplinary and international teams to create richer scientific stories that can describe the functional processes and materials in the different devices, and to plan out strategies to improve their efficiency and stability. This has led to 8 publications in different research journals, 5 conference presentations, 3 patent applications, 2 research proposals and 1 industrial collaboration. 

A quick overview of my projects include:

- Formulation of 16% efficient printable photoactive inks based on low-toxicity environmentally friendly solvents. 
- Design of inkjet printed organic solar cells with transparency values over 50% and efficiencies over 12%. 
- Formulation a conductive ink for humidity resistant photovoltaics. 
- Engineering of solar cell interfaces with improved charge transfer based on solvent additives. 
- Development of a fully printed self-powered system for dopamine and uric acid sensing
- Design of a 3D printing system for solution-based functional materials with 1µl resolution. We used this system to create complex structures for E-skin, Energy Harvesting and  Energy storage applications. 
- Development perovskite single microcrystal on-chip growth strategies for direct-printing of photodetectors and transistors.
jobDescription2:
- Global trainee-ship training in refractory products manufacturing and the steel and cement industries. 
- Development of a Contract Management tool in order to evaluate performance of materials, costs, prices, through which the overall contract performance may help in making decisions for renegotiating with the clients. (Steel Industry)
- Follow-through of client processes, and adaptation of metrics to be used in order to measure material performance. 
- Development of an Inventory Management tool in order to handle material orders, in stock inventory, and scheduling of new orders.

headline: Quality Assurance Engineer
Data Analyst, Business Analyst
company2: King Faisal Specialist Hospital and Research Centre (Gen. Org.)
description:
Throughout my time as a child I had usually a tendency to technology, so I studied Computer Science and I graduated from it with a bachelor's degree. 
As an IT person, I was eager to start my career path and to occupy a position related to my major and my passion, however, I end up with a career that was more related to a business field. 
As the years went by, I found that I was lucky enough to work in a business field with an information technology background. Since I was able to see the business challenges from a different perspective than any other colleague. (Technical side).
This kind of experience expanded my knowledge and gave me a clear vision of what the business expects from IT. So I am always enthusiastic to use my background to leverage the business and making it more efficient and competitive. 

I have worked for five years in the Supply Chain Management department as a Senior Buyer in KFSH&RC. I was responsible for locating and procuring products, supplies, and materials needed by other departments. My job duties helped me to build strong communication skills and taught me various aspects of the business. 
As I mentioned before, working in a business field never let me forgot that I’m an IT person in the first place. And since I was working in a big hospital with over 10,000.00 employees, I found myself dealing with a lot of data.
 
One of the initiatives I made, required me to collect some data to analyze it and extract from it useful information that can be used for business interests. During this process, I found myself thrilled to deal with everything related to data, starting from collecting it, through manipulating and end with visualizing and presenting it in a way that can be easier for the human brain to understand what’s really going on in the business and thus will help for better decision making as well as business enhancement. 
The experience itself that I went through gave me a strong vision of what I want and where I’m going and where I want to be. I am truly fascinated dealing with data and I strongly believe that data is power and it’s the essential element behind the success of any organization if it used wisely.
